definition: to seem/to appear/(in a negative or interrogative sentence) to be sure
to see/to meet/to appear (to be sth)/to interview
structural particle: used after a verb (or adjective as main verb), linking it to following phrase indicating effect, degree, possibility etc
to have to/must/ought to/to need to
to obtain/to get/to gain/to catch (a disease)/proper/suitable/proud/contented/to allow/to permit/ready/finished

sentences.english: This scenery is not very beautiful, but a picture of autumn.
sentences.chinese: 這景色不見得很美，卻是一幅秋日風情畫。

sentences.english: Staying comfortably in the middle of the crowd also cannot guarantee that one is on the right path.
sentences.chinese: 無風無浪的中間路線也不見得會是正途。

sentences.english: Confusion isn’t a bad thing. It means you’re growing and thinking.
sentences.chinese: 困惑不見得是壞事，那表示你在思索和成長。

sentences.english: Most people know it, but they don’t get it.
sentences.chinese: 大部分人知道這一點，但並不見得真正明白。

sentences.english: They don't necessarily have the best teachers or the best, you know, equipment or anything.
sentences.chinese: 他們的老師不一定是最好的，設備什麼的也不見得是。

sentences.english: But lightning must be nasty. Not really.
sentences.chinese: 哦，那閃電可真壞，不見得。

sentences.english: The price of houses is not likely to fall below the present level for some time to come.
sentences.chinese: 房價一時不見得會跌到目前的價格以下。

sentences.english: It doesn’t seem to be the case that high-achieving perfectionists procrastinate more than the rest of us.
sentences.chinese: 成功的完美主義者不見得比其餘的人更容易拖延。

sentences.english: This plot of paddy doesn't seem to be any worse than that one.
sentences.chinese: 這片稻子不見得比那片差。

sentences.english: Miss Xishi was loved widely, while there were some people to love Miss Dongshi.
sentences.chinese: 西施有人愛，東施不見得就沒有人喜歡。

sentences.english: There is no virtue in doing sth.
sentences.chinese: 做某事不見得有什堋好處。

sentences.english: Nor was it much better by the carriage road from Brister's Hill.
sentences.chinese: 從勃立斯特山來的那條馬車路也不見得好多少。

sentences.english: You might not always guess right, but you'll often be "headed" in the right direction.
sentences.chinese: 你不見得都猜得對，但你思想的方向通常是錯不了的。

sentences.english: On our raft we have witnessed this aberration only too well.
sentences.chinese: 我們在筏子上對這些反常天氣見得太多了。

sentences.english: So why do you think the market appears to be on the comeback 30)trail right now?
sentences.chinese: 那麼何以你見得市場現在會有復甦的跡象呢？

definition: let alone/to say nothing of/besides/what's more
at the minimum/at the very least
to say again/to put off a discussion until later/moreover/what's more/besides
to speak the truth/truth to tell/frankly
right/correct/couple/pair/towards/at/for/to face/opposite/to treat (sb a certain way)/to match together/to adjust/to fit/to suit/to answer/to reply/classifier: couple
easy to deal with/not a problem/(polite answer) you flatter me
